song_name: Breath In Breath Out Move On
Breathe In Breathe Out Move On
Burn That Bridge When We Get To It

version_description: You can also do capo 2 and but it up so it is D G and A chords.
Listen to the song first to get a feel... The timing on this is not hard, but it is very important to the song.

More striaght-forward strum pattern than the album version, but it works, especially if you're starting out. I change the strum pattern for the chorus and bridge trying to keep with Buffett's beat on the song.
Added chords to all lines. Corrected lyrics.

I wasn't able to find another chord chart for this song, so I sat down and worked one out myself. The rhythm is a gentle samba or Bossa nova, and the tempo is moderate. X6 and maj9 chords could be simplified if desired: F6 is about the same as Dmaj7, and the Cmaj7 can be substituted for Cmaj9.
